  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6560.85 sitting below the GEX flip at 6583, dealers are long gamma and will mechanically sell any push toward the massive 6580 wall (33.6B) while providing buying support above the 6550 negative gamma zone (-23.8B). The PIN regime combined with this heavy positive gamma concentration between 6565-6580 creates a tight mean-reverting range where dealers will fade moves in both directions. Watch for rejection at 6580 and support around 6565, with any break below 6550 triggering dealer selling that could accelerate moves lower as negative gamma takes over.",
